{"type":null,"faqId":46380,"title":"Huawei Watch_How can I turn on the screen using gestures?","answer":"<a name=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446\"></a><a name=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446\"></a><div id=\"body1442371814968\"><p id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446__p43876663172151\">Yes. You can turn on the screen using wrist gestures, such as by tilting or lifting your wrist.</p><p id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446__p59345654172151\">Touch <span><img src=\"http://app.huawei.com/tkb/ha-i/73456_echot.png\" title=\"click to enlarge\" class=\"imgResize\"></span> in the Android Wear app to access the settings menu, select your Huawei Watch under <strong id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446__b42268668172151\">DEVICE SETTINGS</strong>, and select <strong id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446__b44873693172151\">Tilt to wake screen</strong>.</p><div class=\"note\" id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446__note62320969172210\"><img src=\"http://app.huawei.com/tkb/ha-i/73457_x2ink.gif\"><span class=\"notetitle\"> NOTE: </span><div class=\"notebody\"><p id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757446__p60972703172216\">If you have enabled Theater mode, you can only turn on the screen by pressing the power button.</p></div></div></div><div><div class=\"familylinks\"></div></div>","faqTypeId":334,"faqType":"Screen Display","useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"en-us_topic_0019757446","faqTypeCode":"Wearable_Device-Screen-Display","isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1444638069000,"seriesProductName":"Mercury-G00,Mercury-G01,Mercury-G10","visitedTimes":25,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"turn on, screen, gesture","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}